f=Executive Office/vista/logical/book-requirements.md · p=Logical artifacts Python scripts `Shared OS/logical/` (playbook §13.5) vista imports. Vista owns scripts specific roadmap metrics work inherits cross-agent scripts shared layer. file file folder. · h2:Vista-Specific Scripts (Shared OS/logical/)=\| # \| Script \| Source \| Route \| Domain \| · h2:Vista-Specific Scripts (Shared OS/logical/)=\|---\|--------\|--------\|-------\|--------\| · h2:Vista-Specific Scripts (Shared OS/logical/)=\| 1 \| `signal_detection.py` \| Holmes, Illowsky & Dean, *Introductory Business Statistics* (2nd Ed., 2023, OpenStax, free CC BY) \| A \| Confidence intervals, two-sample tests, minimum sample size, signal vs noise classification, control charts (Western Electric), chi-square goodness-of-fit \| · h2:Vista-Specific Scripts (Shared OS/logical/)=\| 2 \| `rice_prioritization.py` \| Intercom RICE Framework (McBride, 2014) + Reinersten, *The Principles of Product Development Flow* (2009) + SAFe WSJF \| B/C \| RICE scoring, WSJF, cost of delay, effort calibration via planning fallacy, batch prioritization, tie-breaking, sensitivity reports \| · h2:Inherited Scripts (Shared OS/logical/ imported, copied)=\| Script \| Why Vista Needs It \| · h2:Inherited Scripts (Shared OS/logical/ imported, copied)=\|--------\|-------------------\| · h2:Inherited Scripts (Shared OS/logical/ imported, copied)=\| `forecasting.py` \| Time series for metric projections, naive benchmarks for roadmap estimates \| · h2:Inherited Scripts (Shared OS/logical/ imported, copied)=\| `planning_fallacy.py` \| De-bias all roadmap delivery estimates, Bayesian blend, premortem on dates \| · h2:Inherited Scripts (Shared OS/logical/ imported, copied)=\| `investor_metrics.py` \| Cohort analysis tables, metric classification (actionable vs vanity), health dashboard \| · h2:Inherited Scripts (Shared OS/logical/ imported, copied)=\| `capital_budgeting.py` \| NPV/WACC for roadmap investment decisions \| · h2:Inherited Scripts (Shared OS/logical/ imported, copied)=\| `decision_analysis.py` \| MAUT for multi-factor roadmap tradeoffs, sensitivity analysis \| · h2:Inherited Scripts (Shared OS/logical/ imported, copied)=\| `competitive_strategy.py` \| Five forces context for roadmap strategic alignment \| · h2:Inherited Scripts (Shared OS/logical/ imported, copied)=\| `pitch_validation.py` \| Cross-document consistency — roadmap facts match what echo tells investors \| · fc=\| Previously Flagged (0.6) \| Status \| Script \| · fc=\|--------------------------\|--------\|--------\| · fc=\| roadmap-sync: "projected sprint taken as given" \| ✅ Cleared \| `planning_fallacy.py` (Bayesian blend + de_bias_estimate) \| · fc=\| roadmap-sync: "drift calculation without base-rate context" \| ✅ Cleared \| `planning_fallacy.py` (reference_class_statistics + de_bias_estimate) \| · fc=\| rice-prioritization: "Effort estimate optimism bias" \| ✅ Cleared \| `rice_prioritization.py` (calibrate_effort + historical ratios) \| · fc=\| north-star-metric: "metric movement without signal detection" \| ✅ Cleared \| `signal_detection.py` (classify_metric_change, CI, two-sample tests) \| · fc=\| okr-quality-checker: "no statistical grounding for grades" \| ✅ Cleared \| `signal_detection.py` (classify_metric_change, detect_metric_drift) \| · fc=\| roadmap-sync: "drift detection without methodology" \| ✅ Cleared \| `signal_detection.py` (control_limits + Western Electric rules) \| · fc=\| rice-prioritization: "Impact factor calibration" \| ✅ Cleared \| `signal_detection.py` (two-sample tests) + `rice_prioritization.py` (sensitivity_report) \| · sp=**Full time-series statistics** (KPSS test, ADF test, Box-Jenkins methodology, SARIMA) current OpenStax coverage proportions/means/comparison. proper time-series textbook (e.g., Hyndman, already extracted `forecasting.py` focused forecasting hypothesis testing stationarity) add formal stationarity tests. · h2:Skills → Script Mapping=**roadmap-sync** imports `planning_fallacy.py` (Bayesian blend sprint estimates, adjusted slip), `signal_detection.py` (drift detection control charts), **rice-prioritization** imports `rice_prioritization.py` (full RICE engine), `planning_fallacy.py` (effort calibration), `signal_detection.py` (impact calibration), **north-star-metric** imports `signal_detection.py` (classify_metric_change, CI, sample size), `investor_metrics.py` (cohort analysis), **okr-quality-checker** imports `signal_detection.py` (CI-based grading), `forecasting.py` (naive benchmarks projection accuracy)